{"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitableProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitableProtocol\/async_initable_ptr-9q9x9"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitableProtocol\/initAsync(ioPriority:cancellable:callback:userData:)-6ygaj","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitableProtocol\/initAsync(ioPriority:cancellable:callback:userData:)-90jjz","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitableProtocol\/initFinish(res:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitableProtocol\/newFinish(res:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncInitable"},{"type":"text","text":" is an interface for asynchronously initializable objects."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/asyncinitableprotocol"]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"AsyncInitableProtocol"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the asynchronous version of [iface","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"]; it behaves the same"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in all ways except that initialization is asynchronous. For more details"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"see the descriptions on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInitable"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A class may implement both the "},{"code":"GInitable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncInitable"},{"type":"text","text":" interfaces."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Users of objects implementing this are not intended to use the interface"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"method directly; instead it will be used automatically in various ways."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"For C applications you generally just call [func"},{"code":"Gio.AsyncInitable.new_async","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"directly, or indirectly via a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"foo_thing_new_async()"},{"text":" wrapper. This will call","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AsyncInitable.init_async"},{"type":"text","text":"] under the covers, calling back with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NULL"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and a set "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GError"},{"text":" on failure.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A typical implementation might look something like this:"}]},{"code":["enum {","   NOT_INITIALIZED,","   INITIALIZING,","   INITIALIZED","};","","static void","_foo_ready_cb (Foo *self)","{","  GList *l;","","  self->priv->state = INITIALIZED;","","  for (l = self->priv->init_results; l != NULL; l = l->next)","    {","      GTask *task = l->data;","","      if (self->priv->success)","        g_task_return_boolean (task, TRUE);","      else","        g_task_return_new_error (task, ...);","      g_object_unref (task);","    }","","  g_list_free (self->priv->init_results);","  self->priv->init_results = NULL;","}","","static void","foo_init_async (GAsyncInitable       *initable,","                int                   io_priority,","                GCancellable         *cancellable,","                GAsyncReadyCallback   callback,","                gpointer              user_data)","{","  Foo *self = FOO (initable);","  GTask *task;","","  task = g_task_new (initable, cancellable, callback, user_data);","  g_task_set_name (task, G_STRFUNC);","","  switch (self->priv->state)","    {","      case NOT_INITIALIZED:","        _foo_get_ready (self);","        self->priv->init_results = g_list_append (self->priv->init_results,","                                                  task);","        self->priv->state = INITIALIZING;","        break;","      case INITIALIZING:","        self->priv->init_results = g_list_append (self->priv->init_results,","                                                  task);","        break;","      case INITIALIZED:","        if (!self->priv->success)","          g_task_return_new_error (task, ...);","        else","          g_task_return_boolean (task, TRUE);","        g_object_unref (task);","        break;","    }","}","","static gboolean","foo_init_finish (GAsyncInitable       *initable,","                 GAsyncResult         *result,","                 GError              **error)","{","  g_return_val_if_fail (g_task_is_valid (result, initable), FALSE);","","  return g_task_propagate_boolean (G_TASK (result), error);","}","","static void","foo_async_initable_iface_init (gpointer g_iface,","                               gpointer data)","{","  GAsyncInitableIface *iface = g_iface;","","  iface->init_async = foo_init_async;","  iface->init_finish = foo_init_finish;","}"],"syntax":"c","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitableProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text